lasspath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.codehaus.btm:btm:2.1.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"DefaultTransactionManagerLookup discovers Bitronix as its built-in fallback transaction manager, and exercising XA registration/lookup meaningfully requires a concrete transaction manager implementation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.geronimo.specs:geronimo-jms_1.1_spec:1.1.1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Bitronix references JMS APIs through optional classes; adding the JMS spec avoids classpath/native-image analysis failures when Bitronix classes are loaded or analyzed.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Before creating CacheManager/cache instances, disable Ehcache's update check with System.setProperty(\\\"net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck\\\", \\\"true\\\") or equivalent config. For transaction-manager tests, set bitronix.tm.configuration to a temporary properties file with a unique serverId, disableJmx=true, and journal=null; shut down the transaction manager and clear the property after each test. Use temporary diskStore paths and shut down CacheManager instances to avoid cross-test state.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Hibernate, servlet, and Terracotta integration classes have additional provided/external dependencies; avoid those paths unless intentionally adding more setup.\",\n    \"Terracotta clustered-cache coverage would require an external server, but embedded Ehcache core coverage is reachable without Docker.\",\n    \"Bitronix uses JVM-global transaction-manager state, so tests must isolate configuration and cleanup carefully.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f9b374c7a654e0d016a4293d8c5f48190a12dd5c8eccaf63b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1129, "output": 511, "cacheRead": 38400,